==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Iceberg
<hw>Ice"berg`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prob. of Scand.
origin; cf. Dan. <ets>iisbierg</ets>, Sw. <ets>isberg</ets>, properly, a
mountain of ice. See <er>Ice</er>, and <er>Berg</er>.]</ety> <def>A
large mass of ice, generally floating in the ocean.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Icebergs are large detached portions of glaciers, which
in cold regions often project into the sea.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Icebird</ent>⟦br⟧
